<font color="#FF0000">PENSIVE POST</font><br>
<tt>Fri Sep  5 23:16:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet and a few Others:<br><br>
Silent Warrior scared the crap out of me... at first.  I lost a little brother who was a bit too numb... I wish I had him back.  He had the same set of problems we all share... but he couldn't cry or laugh sometimes.  Silent Warrior seemed a little bit anhedonic.  His humorous responses to my B.S. amused me, enlisted my respect... but most of all pleased me.  <br>
Cookie, in my estimation is a little too focused.. serious.. tenacious.  He went from one war into another.  He's had a steady diet of sensation and challenge.  He may experience a delayed PTSD problem.. I hope not.  I am concerned that he now has time to think and recall... his work on his book and papers may be a wonderful type of desensitization or it may create problems.. I had a tough time writing my book.. had to rub my nose in the old feces.  I know that he is tough.. I just hope he is not too tough.  I love sparring with a good man like him... inter-service rivalry is fun outside the barroom.<br>
I admire both of these guys very much... but no more than I do you or Tom and some others.  It's just that I perceive some of you to be cool and stable... and Silent Warrior and Cook are more intense and volatile... like me maybe.  I felt a need to engage them... an attraction of sorts.. with humor and shared ground.  I feel that the three of us have helped one another... I know that they have helped me.  I often wished some others would have joined to help me roll Cook in the dirt or would have come to his side to blaspheme pilots or whatever. I mentioned your name, Chet, in a couple of my silly concoctions... hoping that you might jump in.<br>
If you need to unload on somebody.. it is probably me.  Please try to understand that my displayed lack of seriousness was really not a lack of seriousness at all.<br>
Your posting above is very valid.  Hope I haven't offended you and others.  I spend a lot of time and my money reaching out to troubled veterans.  I have taken in homeless veterans.. gotten them disability compensations and treatment.  I've helped a lot of Native American combat veterans who seem embarrassed to show pain or weakness.  It takes some outreach to get some of these guys out of the pits.<br>
Cook Barela and Silent Warrior are special to me... I don't know why... but it doesn't matter.<br>
I'm not apologizing for my actions... I just hope that explaining them may assage the anger that some feel toward me at the moment.  I, too, am working hard to keep my head above the water.  Your friendship is important to me.<br><br>
Edward Ramon
